Package: cfrnow
Title: Real-Time Case Fatality Ratio via a Mixture-Cure Survival Model
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Sebastian", "Funk", , "sebastian.funk@lshtm.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Estimates a real-time case fatality ratio (CFR) from line-list data
    using a Bayesian mixture-cure survival model, registered as an 'epidist'
    model type so the CFR and the onset-to-death delay both take 'brms'
    formulas. Each case is fatal with probability equal to the CFR and, when
    fatal, dies at an interval-censored onset-to-death delay; cases still alive
    at the observation cut-off are right-censored, which corrects the downward
    bias of the naive deaths / cases ratio in real time. The delay is
    co-estimated using the 'primarycensored' censored-distribution machinery.
